The paper deals with the problem of multi-query optimization, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a greedy algorithm and discusses its approximation factor, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions linear transformations and optimization, which are topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
